clean_description: teen moms tyler baltierra and catelynn lowell vow not to mention carly or her parents anymore  tyler baltierra and catelynn lowellcatelynn lowells latest update on daughter carly has led to some new perspectives on the thursday may  episode of teen mom the next chapter dr drew pinsky had a virtual meeting with the couple to recall a private conversation he had with carlys adoptive parents brandon and teresa davis i can tell you what was expressed to me about carly he shared on the mtv reality shows season finale brandon said she is thriving and she has friends and shes athletic and musical and shes doing all these wonderful things catelynn tried to hold back tears as she wondered why dr drew was sharing the update and not carlys adoptive parents well thanks for keeping that beautiful girl away from me she said while getting visibly emotional dr drew replied i dont think thats the intent i understand thats how it feels i know you i know how tough this is i get it in terms of being unblocked and a visit i dont see that not happening frankly dr drew shared you got to go through the baby steps but you are encouraged to send gifts on christmas birthdays and when gifts are completely appropriate while tyler expressed his belief that its weird to be getting this information from someone other than brandon and teresa dr drew explained that no situation is perfect  what teresa kept saying is she absolutely wants what you want and wants to maintain a relationship but she feels like she needs a reset and for everybody to calm down and let all the negativity settle he said carly sings in church shes quite an accomplished singer and they recorded a song of hers i would love to listen with you because its so moving it does feel like carly is sending a message of im good do you guys want to hear it citing her mental health catelynn said she wanted to listen in private according to mtv when she asked for the link to hear the performance brandon and teresa denied the request  in a joint statement on social media both carly and tyler promised to not speak about carly brandon and teresa publicly moving forward birthparents are always at the mercy of the adopters which is understandable since were the ones who relinquished our baby to them but that still doesnt make it any less hard or painful tyler and catelynn wrote via instagram on thursday as ive stated before we wont be mentioning our biological daughter or her parents anymore  thats why were actually relieved that this episode is airing so that way we can all just finally move forward we are incredibly sorry if anything we have said about our truth as birthparents has hurt you or carly or negatively impacted your life that was never our intention the pair said in a letter to brandon and teresa were the adults here  its our job to put everything aside for the best interest of carly which requires open honest  transparent communication so we hope moving forward
